OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFirst power, now water:    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FSouth Africa's taps run dry
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The peace of a normally tranquil       
OL,6, suburban road near South Africa's      
OL,7, capital, Pretoria, is being shattered  
OL,8, by the sound of drilling.              
OL,10,FThese are not prospectors looking for a
OL,11,Fnew source of the country's mineral    
OL,12,Fwealth, but workers digging for an     
OL,13,Farguably more precious resource: water.
OL,15,FPrivate boreholes - like this one being
OL,16,Fexcavated in Garsfontein - are         
OL,17,Fspringing up across the wealthier      
OL,18,Fneighbourhoods in the country's        
OL,19,Feconomic heartland, where taps have    
OL,20,Fbeen running dry.                      
